HEADWORD: Fetwah
<hw>Fet"wah</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.]</ety> <def>A
written decision of a Turkish mufti some point of law; also applied to
opinions by certain other Islamic religious authorities on points of
Islamic law, such as in Iran.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>fatwah</asp> and <asp>fatwa</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Whitworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
